        "last_activity_date": 1467283684,
        "creation_date": 1467283684,
        "body": "<p>Realm currently doesn't reclaim space on disk automatically, but will instead re-use the space when needed. This means that if you add the objects again, you shouldn't see an increase in file size either.<\/p>\n\n<p>If you want to minimise the size of the file on on disk, you can use <code>Realm.compactRealm(config)<\/code> : <a href=\"https://realm.io/docs/java/latest/api/io/realm/Realm.html#compactRealm-io.realm.RealmConfiguration-\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://realm.io/docs/java/latest/api/io/realm/Realm.html#compactRealm-io.realm.RealmConfiguration-<\/a><\/p>\n",
